But... can&#39;t understand, why you just don&#39;t call your function directly with the code that is changing the value?

Like this..

First the same you have:

    textarea.addEventListener(&#39;input&#39;, adjustSize);

But then, when you change the value just:

    textarea.value = &#39;some new value&#39;;
    adjustSize();

Or better, you can do a function that does everything on the same time (and you will get only one line per call):

    function changeTextarea(newtext : string){
         textarea.value=newtext;
         adjustSize();
    }

So you will have the same effect, without writting 2X lines every time you change the textarea&#39;s value.


(Other possibility is to use jquery like this:)

    $(&quot;#textAreaId&quot;).on(&#39;change&#39;, function(){
         // Do whatever here
    }


Hope this helps!

Because you are making the changes via code, you&#39;ll need to use a [DOM Mutation Observer][1] that can monitor the element for changes. But, don&#39;t set the `value` of the textarea, instead the `value` of a textarea is its content, so set the `textContent`.


&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-js --&gt;

    var textarea = document.getElementById(&#39;myInput&#39;);

    textarea.addEventListener(&#39;input&#39;, adjustSize);

    setTimeout(write, 1000);

    function adjustSize() {
      console.log(&#39;adjustSize&#39;);
    }

    function write() {
      // Don&#39;t set the value, change the content
      textarea.textContent = &#39;new textarea value&#39;;
    }


    // Options for the observer (which mutations to observe)
    const config = { attributes: true, childList: true, subtree: true };

    // Create an observer instance linked to the callback function
    const observer = new MutationObserver(adjustSize);

    // Start observing the target node for configured mutations
    observer.observe(textarea, config);

    // Later, you can stop observing
    //observer.disconnect();

&lt;!-- language: lang-css --&gt;

    .myInput {

    }

&lt;!-- language: lang-html --&gt;

    &lt;textarea id=&quot;myInput&quot; class=&quot;myInput&quot;&gt;
      I am textarea
    &lt;/textarea&gt;

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;


  [1]: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/MutationObserver

